I followed the instructions verbatim a la replacing the hosts file offline, flushing the DNS resolver cache, and replacing all instances of amtlib.dll in the trial install. This is pretty straightforward and I think a lot of people are probably familiar with this approach. I then booted up Wireshark to see if Dreamweaver would make any noise when starting and sure enough it still is able to contact Adobe and transmit some application data despite the measures provided. I used my firewall to block any remaining outbound connections not simply from the program itself but from my computer but it's still not entirely stopping it. I've seen it connect to 192.150.8.200, 192.150.16.60, 192.152.16.200, all Adobe. Not sure how to resolve this. Any suggestions?
